<p>Using the same information from our above calculator, let=E2=80=99s calc=
ulate our strike temperature using John Palmers formula.</p>





<p>W =3D Strike water temperature&nbsp;=C2=B0F (?)<br>R =3D Water to grist =
ratio in quarts/lb ( 40 quarts/14 lbs =3D&nbsp;<strong>2.857</strong>)<br>T=
1 =3D Temp. of your dry grain =C2=B0F (70)<br>T2 =3D Desired mash temp =C2=
=B0F (156 =E2=80=93 adjusted for thermal loss)</p>



<p><strong>W</strong>&nbsp;=3D (.2/R)(T2-T1)+T2</p>



<p>Now to plugin in our values from above into our formula:</p>



<p><strong>W</strong>&nbsp;=3D (.2/2.857)(156-70)+156<br><strong>W</strong>=
&nbsp;=3D (.07)(86)+156</p>



